name: places/ChIJSdS9OsAR2jERTXFNlJIG2iA/reviews/ChdDSUhNMG9nS0VLR1dzN0NNdk9hYXlnRRAB
text: {'text': 'Al-Khair Mosque was founded in the early 1960s. The mosque was built on a hilltop, surrounded by vegetable farms, along Choa Chu Kang Road. Originally named Jamek Mosque, it was later officially renamed as Al-Khair Mosque in 1963. Al-Khair Mosque was then rebuilt under the third phase of the Mosque Building Fund managed by the Islamic Religious Council of Singapore (MUIS). It was operationally ready in 1997, however its official opening was on 31 May 1998. About 15 years later, Al-Khair Mosque went through an 18-month Mosque Upgrading Programme (MUP), this exercise was completed in 2015.', 'languageCode': 'en'}

name: places/ChIJSdS9OsAR2jERTXFNlJIG2iA/reviews/ChdDSUhNMG9nS0VJQ0FnSUNmdXJmdTdBRRAB
text: {'text': 'One of the oldest masjid in Singapore. Moved from the old tech Whye site, the mosque has gone through at least 2 upgrades as it has to cater to more residents living in the CCK area. It is always packed whenever it comes to Hari Raya prayers that the mosque have to do 3 time slots just to accommodate to all worshippers. Very nicely built and adorned with Islamic influence in its designs. The mosque holds many workshops and classes to cater to the Muslim community around it.', 'languageCode': 'en'}

name: places/ChIJSdS9OsAR2jERTXFNlJIG2iA/reviews/ChdDSUhNMG9nS0VJQ0FnSUNUd3B1QzdBRRAB
text:
{'text': 'Practical and prominent mosque.

Located at a junction opposite of the polyclinic, this mosque serves the residents of Chua Chu Kang and more. Very strategically placed as it is very near to the expressway.

The mosque is not as huge as some modern mosques in SG, but it definitely has sufficient space to accommodate guests. The ablution area is just beside the shoe rack, thus easy to find, locate n ready yourself.

Female area is at L2, facilities of cleaning and prayer. There are signages that show the direction.

All in all, we find this mosque, modern, practical and clean.

Thank u for maintaining it very well!', 'languageCode': 'en'}
